HEADWORD: Sleep-at-noon
<hw>Sleep"-at-noon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant (<spn>Tragopogon pratensis</spn>) which closes its flowers
at midday; a kind of goat's beard.</def> <rj><au>Dr.
Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

